snippet: The quake struck Wednesday evening in the Indian Ocean southwest of the Indonesian island of Sumatra, prompting initial concerns of a tsunami.
abstract: Strong earthquake hits Indian Ocean southwest of Indonesian island Sumatra; no deaths or extensive damage are reported.
lead_paragraph: The quake struck Wednesday evening in the Indian Ocean southwest of the Indonesian island of Sumatra, prompting initial concerns of a tsunami.

headline.main: Big Earthquake Strikes Off Indonesia; Little Damage Reported
headline.print_headline: World Briefing | Asia; Indonesia: Quake Strikes Near Sumatra
